Just as we return from our September ride, weâ€™re thrilled to announce our next voyage on the ferry of queer love, lust, and stunning music: Cruise. While no journey is ever quite the same, the coordinates remain consistent: sterling Techno on our BLITZ floor and sensual House grooves on our PLUS floor, all for our grown, empathic, and ecstatic Cruise community.

On the BLITZ floor, expect a spellbinding lineup of essential Techno selectors. Freddy K, head of Key Vinyl and self-proclaimed > Techno Activist < needs no introduction. Heâ€™s a revered ambassador of timeless Techno, delivering functional grooves infused with soul, warmth, and a staggering sense of swing. Joining him is our resident Polygonia, who channels otherworldly soundscapes, crafting a fresh vision of Deep Techno with intricate textures. Rising star Quelza, representing a new wave of Techno DJs and producers, brings his cinematic twist to the genre, demonstrating that intensity isnâ€™t just about fast BPMsâ€”itâ€™s about creating captivating sonic journeys. With a nod to the opiate Dub Techno she first (re-)introduced in her native Lyon, Olivia Mendez spins narcotic grooves with a rough and ready take on contemporary Techno that delights with rousing, rigid grooves and winsome woozyness.

Over on the PLUS floor, we begin with the well-tuned duo Katia Curie and Nizar Sarakbi. These two members of Viennaâ€™s Sonic Resistance collective share a love for late '90s and early '00s House & Techno, as well as their native Kyiv influences, and will showcase the lighter, more playful side of their sound. Closing out the night, Ibiza-based selector Pascal Moscheni offers a dose of summertime nostalgia and estival blending dreamy Italo Disco, disco-inflected grooves, golden-era Tech House, and sun-drenched, estival euphoria, transporting us back to balmy Balearic evenings.

Ritournelle is back for a night of intelligent dance music in the literal sense of the word! Blurring borders between club culture and experimentalism and marrying hedonism with leftfield exploration, Ritournelle unites the ravers, nerds, and all those with a taste for sensation! Powered by Blitz Clubâ€™s peerless acoustic design and sound system, Ritournelle celebrates its 12th year and promises stunning live performances and ravishing DJ sets.

From esteemed and reunited pioneers who have shaped club culture to young and adventurous talents rewriting electronic dance music and its culture, the party merges the past with the present. The soundtrack to this club-orientated Ritournelle edition comes from soaring upstarts to revered veterans. 

Such as: the British Murder Boys, the seminal live-duo formed by the two UK-paragons Surgeon and Regis. Theyâ€™re back and finally released their debut album this year, long after their last split, full of >. industrial dub techno assault < madness, to quote The Quietus. Or Aunty Rayzor, the young Nigerian sonic trailblazer with her euphoric blend of Afrobeat, R&B, hip-hop, pop, grime, and experimental sounds. Also on the lineup: Helena Hauff, Hamburgâ€™s queen of black magic dance music, who will be spinning an electrifying mix of Techno, Acid, and Electroâ€”all on vinyl, of course. Kicking off the night, Jonas Friedlich will set the mood with his dizzying and beguiling take on breaky, mashed up funk. Merging the eclectic mix of performers and music is the idiosyncratic Berlin duo Modeselektor, who have been championing crossover sounds and the wide open playing field of electronic dance music for decades, uniting techno heads & indie kids, ravers & critics on the dancefloor with a singular and cosmopolitan take on dance music.  

Revel in the anticipation of new experiences and newfound favorites to be discovered! Mark your calendar for Friday, the 18th of October, and usher in a night of sonic spectacle beyond the borders of what dance music can express.

Jazzfest and Blitz Club team up for the third time to celebrate not just one, but two evenings of Munichâ€™s Jazzfest this November! Blitzâ€™s high-precision sound and room design and Jazz musicâ€™s highly refined, present day musicianship prove to be a fruitful combination and weâ€™re happy to open our doors for another evening full of stunning and current crossover-jazz blends that scrape dance music, pop and many more influences.

Mr. Vertigo
Mr. Vertigo is modern power-groove music, combining the sophistication of jazz, the melancholy of indie rock, and the lightness of pop. Drummers Daniel Mudrack and Florian Haas alternate between playing in unison and weaving intricate rhythms, creating a rhythmic foundation for Ursus Bachthaler (Stratocaster) and Thomas Bauser (keys) to develop their expressive solos. Their performances are grounded by a warm, agile bass that ties the music together yet propels it forward. Ursus Bachthaler has dedicated several of his compositions to musicians who have accompanied and influenced him over the past decade.
